%D A261671 Although the OEIS indexes sequences by consecutive integers, it is better to think of this sequence as defined on the odd numbers 1,3,5,7,... and given by f(4m+1)=12m+3, f(4m+3)=2m+1, that is, subtract 1 and divide by 2 if the result is odd, otherwise multiply by 3. This arises in analyzing A109732.
%D A261671 It is conjectured that starting with any positive odd number d and iterating f, we always eventually reach either 1, 9, or 33 (see Comments in A135730).
